<% content_for :title, "About — Torren Clifford" %>

<div class="page-content">
  <h1>About</h1>

  <p>
    Torren Clifford is a Melbourne-based designer and maker originally from Perth, and the
    founder of manufacturing and design studio Old Four Legs.
  </p>

  <p>
    A challenge-driven practitioner, Torren has found his personal mark by pursuing the
    unachievable — through rigorous design practice and material experimentation. His creative
    process explores the tension between organic texture and purposeful line, working across a
    broad spectrum of techniques and materials to arrive at objects that feel both inevitable
    and surprising.
  </p>

  <p>
    At the upcoming VDB, Clifford presents <em>Speleothem Chair</em> — a piece from the
    <em>Sedimental</em> series, cast in recycled aluminium. Drawing from natural landscapes,
    country, and the slow violence of erosion, the work reflects minerals back into story and
    shape; geology made legible through the human hand.
  </p>

  <p>
    Like ruins, Old Four Legs' objects naturalise themselves into the landscape of the future.
    Beyond the divide of nature and culture, they are an alchemy — human-made metal
    transcended into a sublime neo-nature. They exist on the spectrum between fear and hope,
    suspended in the same existential surrender we offer to the wild: beyond extinction,
    beyond salvation, simply present.
  </p>

